<item>
            <title>[LU-14181] sanity test_64e fails with SHARED_KEY on RHEL/CentOS 8.2</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14181</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for S Buisson &amp;lt;sbuisson@ddn.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/2e038072-2f42-4dca-bb3d-ce025d30fbaa&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/2e038072-2f42-4dca-bb3d-ce025d30fbaa&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test_64e failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;init grants: grants mismatch: 0, expected 2146304
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This happens with any SSK flavor when client runs on RHEL/CentOS 8.2.&lt;/p&gt;





&lt;p&gt;VVVVVVV DO NOT REMOVE LINES BELOW, Added by Maloo for auto-association VVVVVVV&lt;br/&gt;
sanity test_64e - init grants: grants mismatch: 0, expected 2146304&lt;/p&gt;</description>
